ELDORET, KENYA: The Kenya Revenue Authority (KRA) has destroyed illegally imported goods worth Sh1 million that had been seized at the Eldoret International Airport. The goods, which included sex toys, toy guns, tobacco and seed products, were seized one year ago at the airport. &nbsp;Speaking during the exercise at the Moi Teaching and Referral Hospital, KRA Deputy Commissioner Florence Otwory, said goods such as toy guns could enhance criminal activities. &nbsp; ALSO READ: Five reasons it&rsquo;s easier to get through this year&rsquo;s tax season